vision.notes: Visual capabilities are unknown based on available information.

mechanoreception.notes: As crustaceans, Tulumellidae likely possess mechanoreceptors for detecting water movement and vibrations. This is crucial for orientation and prey detection in their aquatic environment.

chemoreception.notes: Crustaceans generally rely on chemoreception for finding food and mates in aquatic environments. Tulumellidae likely use chemoreceptors to navigate their surroundings.
